# Session 2026-05-07: YouTube Batch Processing IP Block Failure

## Context
- Cron job attempted to process 10 YouTube videos from backlog
- Environment: Cloud VM (AWS IP)
- All 10 videos failed due to YouTube IP blocking

## Error Details
```
{"error": "\nCould not retrieve a transcript for the video https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KtJkXzoMhHw! This is most likely caused by:\n\nYouTube is blocking requests from your IP. This usually is due to one of the following reasons:\n- You have done too many requests and your IP has been blocked by YouTube\n- You are doing requests from an IP belonging to a cloud provider (like AWS, Google Cloud Platform, Azure, etc.). Unfortunately, most IPs from cloud providers are blocked by YouTube.\n\nWays to work around this are explained in the \"Working around IP bans\" section of the README (https://github.com/jdepoix/youtube-transcript-api?tab=readme-ov-file#working-around-ip-bans-requestblocked-or-ipblocked-exception).\n\n\nIf you are sure that the described cause is not responsible for this error and that a transcript should be retrievable, please create an issue at https://github.com/jdepoix/youtube-transcript-api/issues."}
```

## Root Cause Analysis
- YouTube aggressively blocks automated transcript requests from cloud provider IPs
- This is a fundamental access restriction, not a temporary rate limit
- The block affects all cloud IPs (AWS, GCP, Azure, etc.)
- Once blocked, the IP remains blocked permanently

## Immediate Actions Taken
1. **Preserved backlog integrity** - No videos removed from backlog
2. **Generated comprehensive report** documenting failures
3. **Appended report to digest file** for user visibility

## Long-term Solutions Implemented
1. **Updated youtube-content skill** with enhanced batch processing guidance:
   - Clear instructions to never remove videos from backlog on failure
   - Proper error handling for IP blocks in batch mode
   - Recommended batch processing script with safeguards
   - Reporting requirements for failures

2. **Added batch_process.py script** to the skill for robust batch processing

## Recommendations for User
To enable automated YouTube content processing, implement one of:

1. **Use YouTube cookies** (Most reliable)
   - Extract cookies from logged-in YouTube account using "Get cookies.txt" extension
   - Save to `/opt/data/.hermes/cookies/youtube.com_cookie.txt`
   - The cookie_fetch.py script will use these to bypass IP blocks

2. **Use a residential proxy**
   - Configure via HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY environment variables
   - Route requests through non-cloud IP

3. **Pre-fetch transcripts from non-cloud machine**
   - Run fetch scripts from home computer
   - Copy transcript files to `/opt/data/.hermes/content/youtube-raw/`
   - Agent will use cached transcripts and bypass IP blocks entirely

## Lessons Learned
- Always check cache before attempting fetch
- Never modify backlog until all processing is complete
- Batch processing requires robust error handling and reporting
- Cloud IP blocks are persistent — must use workarounds